President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Christopher Miller for the position of Director of the National Counterterrorism Center, Office of the Director of National Intelligence. Currently serving as the Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Special Operations and Combating Terrorism, Mr. Miller is responsible for developing policy guidance and overseeing the implementation of Department of Defense policies related to special operations and combating terrorism. Prior to this role, he served as a Special Assistant to the President for Counterterrorism on the National Security Council and held positions in intelligence oversight and sensitive special operations advisory in the Office of the Secretary of Defense. With over three decades of experience in the United States Army Special Forces, Mr. Miller has received multiple awards for his service, including the Legion of Merit and three Bronze Stars. He holds a B.A. in History from George Washington University and an M.A. in National Security Studies from the Naval War College.